Grammar

Rule 0     S' -> program
Rule 1     program -> statement_list
Rule 2     statement_list -> statement_list statement
Rule 3     statement_list -> statement
Rule 4     statement -> DECL TYPE ID ASSIGN expression
Rule 5     statement -> PRINT ID
Rule 6     expression -> expression PLUS expression
Rule 7     expression -> expression MINUS expression
Rule 8     expression -> expression TIMES expression
Rule 9     expression -> expression DIVIDE expression
Rule 10    expression -> NUMBER
Rule 11    expression -> ID

Terminals, with rules where they appear

ASSIGN               : 4
DECL                 : 4
DIVIDE               : 9
ID                   : 4 5 11
MINUS                : 7
NUMBER               : 10
PLUS                 : 6
PRINT                : 5
TIMES                : 8
TYPE                 : 4
error                : 

Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

expression           : 4 6 6 7 7 8 8 9 9
program              : 0
statement            : 2 3
statement_list       : 1 2

Parsing method: LALR

state 0

    (0) S' -> . program
    (1) program -> . statement_list
    (2) statement_list -> . statement_list statement
    (3) statement_list -> . statement
    (4) statement -> . DECL TYPE ID ASSIGN expression
    (5) statement -> . PRINT ID

    DECL            shift and go to state 4
    PRINT           shift and go to state 5

    program                        shift and go to state 1
    statement_list                 shift and go to state 2
    statement                      shift and go to state 3

